him-apN 
A thing that one meditates, purposes, or intends to do; or that one desires to do; or endeavours to do; a purpose; an intention; or an object of desire, or of endeavour; 
as also ham-apN↓. (JK, Ḳ.)

huw-apN 
A deep hollow in the ground: (Ṣ, JK, M, Mṣb, Ḳ:) or a hollow, or cavity, in the ground; a pit: (Mṣb:) or a descent in the ground: (Ḳ:) or a deep hollow, cavity, or pit; 
as also mahowaApN↓: or a low, or depressed, place in the ground. (TA.)
